# React Components

## File organization

- Each component lives in its own folder or alongside a co-located CSS Module:
  - Simple: `components/Button.tsx` + `components/Button.module.css`
  - Complex: `components/Editor/MDXEditor.tsx` + `components/Editor/MDXEditor.module.css` + `components/Editor/index.ts`
- Storybook stories live next to the component: `Component.stories.tsx`.
- Re-export public components from `apps/admin/src/components/index.ts` (barrel).

## Styling

- Use **CSS Modules only** (`.module.css`); no inline styles for layout/colors, no Tailwind, no global classes.
- Use design tokens (CSS custom properties) — never hard-code colors, sizes, spacing, or radii:
  - Colors: `var(--accent)`, `var(--bg-primary)`, `var(--text-primary)`, `var(--border-strong)`, `var(--error)`, …
  - Spacing: `var(--space-1..6)`. Radii: `var(--radius-sm|md)`. Type: `var(--text-sm|base)`, `var(--font-medium)`.
  - Motion: `var(--transition-fast)`, and always include a `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` fallback for animations.

## Component API

- Functional components only. Props extend the underlying HTML element props when the component wraps one:

```tsx
interface ButtonProps extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'ghost' | 'danger'
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg'
  loading?: boolean
}
```

- Compose class names with a `[styles.x, condition && styles.y, className].filter(Boolean).join(' ')` pattern.
- Forward unknown props with a typed spread; never silently drop `className` or `aria-*`.

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA — required)

- Every interactive element needs a visible `:focus-visible` style.
- Modals: implement focus trap, close on Escape, `role="dialog"` + `aria-labelledby`.
- Use `aria-expanded`, `aria-current`, `aria-live` where appropriate; loading spinners are decorative (`aria-hidden="true"`).
- Disabled/loading buttons: set both `disabled` and `aria-disabled`.
- Use the `.sr-only` utility class for screen-reader-only text.
- Icon-only buttons must have `aria-label`.
